element.description:
The reverse of the Name enchantment. A magical item with a Password functions unless the Password is spoken. If the Password is spoken, the item will be inert until the next time its powers would normally be invoked – or for one minute (choice of person making the item). An item may have some spells that are passworded and others that are not.

Examples:
(a) a magic ring that gave the power of flight – but puts the wearer in Suspended Animation unless the password was used;
(b) a Pentagram that can be “turned off” with a word;
(c) a Dancing Sword that stops swinging for one minute if the password is said.

Cannot be removed unless the spells it limits are also removed.

Creates a brilliant flash of light. This will totally blind some that see it, and reduce the DX of others by 3 (which reduces all DX-based skills). It may affect anyone who is facing the flash and has his eyes open (GM’s decision, if miniatures are not being used). The caster himself is not affected if he closes his eyes as he casts the spell. Each other creature in range must make a HT roll to avoid the worst effects:

Within 10 yards: on a success, 1 minute at -3 DX; on a failure, 3 seconds blindness and 1 minute at -3 DX;
11 to 25 yards: on a success, 10 seconds at -3 DX; on a failure, 1 minute at -3 DX;
26 or more yards: on a success, no effects; on a failure, 3 seconds at -3 DX.
